latestIgtvVideos.title: July Favourites! 🌞
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Products mentioned 👇🏻

- @cosrx Salicylic Acid Gentle Cleanser

I’ve been liking this a lot! It has a slight fragrance but i don’t mind it. Cleanses well and doesn’t strip the skin. 

- @laneigeindia Cream Skin Toner

This toner is sooooo hydrating! You have to pick this up if you’re a dry skin type. I personally don’t find it THAT affordable, but it’s worth the 💰

- @snp.korea Peptaronic Serum

The fragrance is sooo calming. This is actually very hydrating and I’m enjoying this during the monsoon since my skin tends to get dry patches around this time of the year.

- @drsheths Ashwagandha & Alpha Arbutin Serum

Pick this up if you have hyperpigmentation. Just do it. Visible difference in 2 weeks. I love it!!! It also has a great formula that tightens and soothes your skin. 

- @aderma_france Rheacalm Soothing Cream

Holy Grail moisturiser. I had already finished a tube way back. I repurchased this because I found nothing like it. 

@beminimalist__ Vitamin C 10% + AG 1% Serum

Finished my bottle. Love the texture, it’s slightly sticky. I can’t maintain the bottles as you can tell lmao. Works very well for pigmentation and overall glow. Takes time to show results though.

- @lashieldofficial Sunscreen Gel SPF 40 PA+++

The only sunscreen that makes me feel like it’s protecting my skin. I usually hate applying SPF but i have to. So i do it. This one helps. It’s super lightweight and glides on like a dream leaving no whitecast. 

- @theearthrhythm Lip & Cheek Tint in Mermaid
 
I use this everyday because it gives my cheeks such a nice flush. It doesn’t stay on that long though. The texture is slightly thick compared to regular tints, so I wouldn’t recommend acne prone, oily skin types to use this. If you have dry skin, 100% go for it. 

Do you guys enjoy this idea? Tell me in the comments!💕

#beautyfavourites #budgetbeauty #skincarefaves #skincare #indianskincare #indianbrands #koreanskincare
